Out of the 6-hour window, I was only able to utilize around 45 minutes to solve problems due to repeated server issues. TCSCodeVita, this experience needs to be addressed. Such issues during a competitive coding event diminish the credibility of the competition

In the end, I could solve only 1 out of 6 questions. It wasn‚Äôt about how many I solved but about how the competition wasn‚Äôt fair. Many participants like me faced server issues, making the experience frustrating and demoralizing.

This cycle repeated for over 1.5 hours. Login issues, session timeouts, and unresponsive servers wasted my time. By 2 PM, I had almost lost hope. Even though the site started working normally, I had barely any time left to complete the exam.

This led to a message saying I had "two active sessions" ‚Äì one for the questions and one for the compiler. It logged me out, showing a "session expired" message. There was an option to log out all sessions, but it didn‚Äôt work. I had to wait 15 minutes before trying again

This led to a message saying I had "two active sessions" ‚Äì one for the questions and one for the compiler. It logged me out, showing a "session expired" message. There was an option to log out all sessions, but it didn‚Äôt work. I had to wait 15 minutes before trying again

This issue persisted until around 12 PM. By then, I was finally able to log in, but a new problem surfaced. I could log in, but the questions wouldn‚Äôt load. When I opened their online compiler, it opened in a new tab, but the main page refreshed again

At around 9:20 AM, as I tried to submit my first answer, the page refreshed. When I attempted to log in again, the site stopped responding. I kept trying but failed. I reached out to a friend, and he was facing the same issue. It felt unfair as the servers weren‚Äôt cooperating. https://t.co/VxCrHeMRhJ

The window for the TCSCodeVita exam was open from 15th Nov, 3 PM to 16th Nov, 3 PM. Due to unavoidable circumstances, I planned to give the exam on 16th Nov from 9 AM to 3 PM. Everything seemed fine initially, but then things started falling apart. Here's my experience üßµüëá

Now I realize, TCSCodeVita is hard‚Äînot because the questions are tough, but because the experience is.
